<!-- SECTION 2: UV LAB -->
<section id="uv-lab">
<div class="section-label hidden">Section 02</div>
<h2 class="section-title hidden">UV Map <span>Laboratory</span></h2>
<p class="section-sub hidden">UV coordinates are the address system every shader uses to locate each pixel. U runs left→right, V runs bottom→top, both in range 0.0–1.0.</p>
<div class="controls-row hidden stagger-1">
<button class="ctrl-btn active" onclick="setUVMode('normal',this)">Default UV</button>
<button class="ctrl-btn" onclick="setUVMode('tile',this)">Tile ×4</button>
<button class="ctrl-btn" onclick="setUVMode('center',this)">Center</button>
<button class="ctrl-btn" onclick="setUVMode('rotate',this)">Rotate</button>
<button class="ctrl-btn" onclick="setUVMode('polar',this)">Polar</button>
</div>
<div class="uv-split hidden stagger-2">
<div style="position:relative;">
<div class="canvas-wrap">
<canvas height="360" id="uv-canvas" style="width:100%;cursor:crosshair;" width="480"></canvas>
<div class="uv-tooltip-canvas" id="uv-tooltip">U: 0.00  V: 0.00</div>
</div>
</div>
<div>
<h4 style="font-size:0.85rem;color:var(--text);margin-bottom:0.5rem;">Fragment Shader</h4>
<div class="code-panel" id="uv-code-panel" style="height:200px;font-size:0.72rem;">
<span class="glsl-comment">// Default UV display</span><br/>
<span class="glsl-type">vec2</span> uv = vUv;<br/>
        gl_FragColor = <span class="glsl-fn">vec4</span>(uv.x, uv.y, <span class="glsl-num">0.3</span>, <span class="glsl-num">1.0</span>);
      </div>
<div class="edu-card" style="margin-top:0.75rem;font-size:0.82rem;">
<strong>UV coordinates</strong> map texture space onto geometry. In a fullscreen quad shader, U=red (horizontal), V=green (vertical). The black corner is (0,0), the white corner is (1,1).
      </div>
</div>
</div>
</section>
<!-- SECTION 3: SINE WAVE WORLD -->
<section id="sine-world">
<div class="section-label hidden">Section 03</div>
<h2 class="section-title hidden">Sine <span>Wave World</span></h2>
<p class="section-sub hidden">sin() is the atom of visual programming. From it: waves, rotations, oscillations, organic motion — and every VJ effect you've ever loved.</p>
<div class="canvas-wrap hidden stagger-1" style="margin-bottom:1rem;">
<canvas height="280" id="sine-canvas" style="width:100%;" width="700"></canvas>
</div>
<div class="formula-box" id="sine-formula">sin(uv.x × 6.28 + time × 1.0) × 0.30 + 0.00</div>
<div class="hidden stagger-2">
<div class="slider-row">
<label>Amplitude</label>
<input id="sine-amp" max="0.48" min="0.01" step="0.01" type="range" value="0.3"/>
<span class="slider-val" id="sine-amp-v">0.30</span>
</div>
<div class="slider-row">
<label>Frequency</label>
<input id="sine-freq" max="20" min="1" step="0.5" type="range" value="2"/>
<span class="slider-val" id="sine-freq-v">2.0</span>
</div>
<div class="slider-row">
<label>Speed</label>
<input id="sine-speed" max="5" min="0" step="0.1" type="range" value="1.0"/>
<span class="slider-val" id="sine-speed-v">1.0</span>
</div>
<div class="slider-row">
<label>Offset</label>
<input id="sine-offset" max="0.5" min="-0.5" step="0.01" type="range" value="0"/>
<span class="slider-val" id="sine-offset-v">0.00</span>
</div>
<div class="controls-row" style="margin-top:0.5rem;">
<button class="ctrl-btn" id="sine-dual-btn" onclick="toggleDualWave()">+ Second Wave (Interference)</button>
</div>
</div>
<div class="edu-card hidden stagger-3">
<strong>Key insight:</strong> Every shader effect — water reflections, audio visualizers, organic motion — is built from sin/cos combinations. The interference pattern of two overlapping waves creates beating, modulation, and the appearance of complex life.
  </div>
</section>
